(
<emphasis box="[1030,1054,784,807]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">X.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1068,1165,784,807]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">virgulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1179,1264,783,807]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,853,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Abdomen yellow, terga somewhat brownish on the lateral margins, with more or less visible brownish spot dorsally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,853,1459]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Hypopygium. Cercus with wide dorsal projection bearing numerous distinct setae, epandrium subtriangular with strong, long dorsal setae subapically and apically, hypandrium membranous basally with subapical pair of fine, short setae, phallus upcurved, rather long.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,853,1459]" box="[197,931,1046,1072]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Female similar to male except for the usual sexual differences.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
